# Copilot development workflow

When you change anything under copilot routing, HMITL UI, eval dataset, or related server actions, **always run the copilot test bundle before claiming the work is done**.

## Required command

```bash
pnpm run test:copilot
```

This runs:

1. `pnpm run eval:hmitl` — labeled router safety gate (0 false auto-send, 0 RAG/blacklist auto_send)
2. Vitest — all `tests/int/copilot*.int.spec.*` integration tests

## Also run when appropriate

- After schema changes: `pnpm run generate:types` then `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit`
- Before disabling shadow mode or widening `autoSendAllowlist`: `pnpm run eval:hmitl` must pass on the full dataset

## Adding regression cases

If manual testing finds a mis-route, add a case to `tests/eval/hmitl_eval_dataset.ts` before fixing the router.

## Do not skip because

- Integration tests alone do not measure false auto-send rate across the labeled set
- `eval:hmitl` is the go-live gate documented in `docs/plans/2026-05-17-ai-hmitl-router-plan.md`
